[2.227602, "o", "╭───────── Ralph Workflow ──────────╮\r\n│  ____       _       _     _       │\r\n│ |  _ \\ __ _| |_ __ | |__ | |__    │\r\n│ | |_) / _` | | '_ \\| '_ \\| '_ \\   │\r\n│ |  _ < (_| | | |_) | | | | | | |  │\r\n│ |_| \\_\\__,_|_| .__/|_| |_|_| |_|  │\r\n│               |_|                 │\r\n╰───────────── v0.8.8 ──────────────╯\r\nWelcome to Ralph Workflow\r\nPROMPT-driven agent orchestrator\r\n"]
[2.234896, "o", "╭─────────────────────── Ralph Workflow first-run setup ───────────────────────╮\r\n│                                                                              │\r\n│  Ralph Workflow orchestrates AI coding agents through a planning →           │\r\n│  development loop driven by your PROMPT.md.                                  │\r\n│  New to Ralph Workflow? Read docs/sphinx/getting-started.md for a            │\r\n│  step-by-step walkthrough.                                                   │\r\n│  Offline docs: python -m pydoc ralph · run make serve-docs from              │\r\n│  ralph-workflow/ for the full HTML reference.                                │\r\n│                                                                              │\r\n│  Ensure your AI agents are on PATH (e.g., `claude`, `opencode`, `agy`)       │\r\n│  Local config files:                                                         │\r\n│    • mcp.toml                                                                │\r\n│    • pipeline.toml                                                           │\r\n│    • artifacts.toml                                                          │\r\n│  Next steps:                                                                 │\r\n│    1. Edit PROMPT.md with your implementation task                           │\r\n│    2. Install AI agents if missing (e.g., `claude`, `opencode`, `agy`)       │\r\n│    3. (Optional) Run ralph --init-local-config when this repo needs an       │\r\n│  optional full project-local override copy of the user-global config set     │\r\n│    4. (Recommended) Run ralph --diagnose to verify agents, MCP servers, and  │\r\n│  config before the first real run                                            │\r\n│    5. Run ralph to start the pipeline                                        │\r\n│    6. Run `ralph --regenerate-config` to reset configs                       │\r\n│    7. ⭐ Star https://codeberg.org/RalphWorkflow/Ralph-Workflow so we know   │\r\n│  you're using it — stars drive development priority                          │\r\n│  Error reporting: Ralph Workflow sends anonymous crash data and performance  │\r\n│  metrics. No personal data is collected. See                                 │\r\n│  ~/.config/ralph-workflow-user.ini for details.                              │\r\n│                                                                              │\r\n│  ⭐ Star https://codeberg.org/RalphWorkflow/Ralph-Workflow so we know        │\r\n│  you're using it — stars drive development priority                          │\r\n│                                                                              │\r\n"]
[2.234977, "o", "╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\r\n"]
